                <p>Bosch cooktops are celebrated for their sleek design and high performance. However, these high-end appliances often come with a higher repair cost, usually between <b>$200 and $500</b>. Problems can range from malfunctioning touch controls to issues with induction elements or gas valves. Given the advanced technology used in Bosch cooktops, repairs often require specialized knowledge and parts, contributing to the higher cost. Authorized Bosch service centers are recommended for any repairs to ensure that the work meets the brand's high standards and to keep warranties intact.</p>

