                <p>Samsung cooktops, known for their innovative features and modern aesthetics, generally have repair costs ranging from <b>$150 to $400</b>. Common issues include defective touch controls, malfunctioning burners, and sensor errors. The cost of repairs depends on the complexity of the problem and the specific model. For instance, fixing a basic gas burner issue might be relatively inexpensive, while troubleshooting an advanced induction cooktop could be more costly. Samsung provides a network of authorized service centers that can ensure quality repairs and help preserve any warranties.</p>

                <h3>KitchenAid</h3>
                <p>KitchenAid cooktops are favored for their robust build and professional-grade features. Repair costs for KitchenAid cooktops typically range from <b>$150 to $450</b>. Frequent issues include broken heating elements, faulty ignition systems, and control panel malfunctions. While basic repairs such as replacing a heating element might be on the lower end of the cost spectrum, more complex issues involving the control panel or electronic components can be more expensive. To ensure high-quality repairs and maintain any existing warranties, it’s best to use certified KitchenAid technicians.</p>

                <h3>LG</h3>
                <p>LG cooktops are renowned for their advanced technology and stylish designs. Repair costs for LG cooktops usually range between <b>$150 and $400</b>. Common problems include malfunctioning touch controls, burner issues, and sensor errors. Simpler repairs, like replacing a burner, tend to be less costly, whereas resolving electronic or sensor-related issues can be more expensive. LG has a network of authorized service centers that can provide reliable repairs, ensuring the longevity of the appliance and the validity of any warranties.</p>

